div.p:
The texts are made available in a double presentation:
on the one hand, as a diplomatic transcription, preserving the historical particularities of the source, such as abbreviations, original spellings, accentuation, word unions, punctuation marks and obvious errors;
on the other hand, as a standardised text, resolving abbreviations, regularizing spelling, accentuation, word spacing and punctuation, and correcting obvious errors in order to improve the readability of the text.
